In fact, I remember the name was specfically coined by a user in the original thread in early October, who posted a cool red match box striking graphic.

Honestly, I think it was just aâ€¦ https://t.co/ekCfpIH9aP

Originally, I was going to collaborate with Team Liquid on this project since I figured it could use larger backing or infrastructure.

Anyway - during the calls I asked about the platforms, the features, etc.

So, November came around I was able to use SmashPros A LOT. 

The reason I ended up going with SmashPros was  that they had a working product with many top players already using it + vouching for it.

The fact that I could use it myself, grind on it, and see my ELO go up and down on a lightweight website with no fluff appealed to me heavily.

Matchpoint was still building the site, which is totally understandable. 

At that time, I just felt more secure putting my stamp ofâ€¦

And that's pretty much the long and short of it. 

Matchbox isn't made for profit or anything like that, nor am I getting paid for supporting it at all.

it's just a useful website for the community that asked if they could use my brand and platform for support.

If they wantedâ€¦

To finalize on this:

I was able to see some of the early beta images of Matchpoint and it honestly looks great. From what I understand it even has features like Bo5 Rank toggle and Global Matchmaking toggles.

There doesn't just have to be one ladder for all this - everyone whoâ€¦

I will gladly be using both ladders, full stop.

I don't see this as a competition at all. It's rather a chance to create the best platform possible for connecting players who want to improve.

I encourage everyone to follow @MatchpointGG_ and use their platform as well when itâ€¦
